	        Send us your pictures   ·  Send us your stories Fire fighters and residents of Alexandra are fighting a blaze which has engulfed several shacks. The cause of the fire is currently unknown, but emergency personnel are on site. Johannesburg Emergency Services spokesperson Nana Radebe told News24 that the fire was between London and 22nd streets. She could not confirm how many shacks had been affected at this stage. "For now we have asked community members to assist us in confirming if all their neighbours have been accounted for, as we work towards putting the fire out." More to follow. A fire has broken out in Alexandra, Johannesburg. Fire fighters battling to control the blaze. @eNCA reporter @malungelob is on the ground. A local councillor says 500 shacks have been affected. Let’s pray for #Alexandra #Alexfire pic.twitter.com/1gQJVocHoW London road, Alexandra #Alexfire pic.twitter.com/Tn5hXemoUa #AlexFire some of this people are at work they will come back home to find that there is no home @Harman_Mashaba @CityofJoburgZA @Julius_S_Malema   24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  